<br><h2 class=3D"title_grn">Definition: Mile</h2>
<p>A mile is any of several units of distance, or, in physics terminology, =
of length.  Today, one mile is mainly equal to about 1609 m on land and 185=
2 m at sea and in the air, but see below for the details.  The abbreviation=
 for mile is 'mi'.  There are more specific definitions of 'mile' such as t=
he metric mile, statute mile, nautical mile, and survey mile.  On this site=
, we assume that if you only specify 'mile' you want the statute mile.</p>


